snippet.textDisplay:
The #beauty about #words is they can mean any number of things depending on whom you ask - even if by #definition there is only one meaning. #Human beings are complex and our languages are just as complex. And evolve just as we do.

The beauty of @ronnieradke reinventing and releasing this song (The Drug In Me Is Reimagined) goes to show just how true my words ring. He has taken a #song from my past, his past, and reusing the same words spoke a whole new story to every soul out there who, more than likely, has evolved along side with us and this song.

This #reinvention you have #brilliantly expressed here Ronnie, shows the growth in your musical expertise. As well as given the rest of us a grown up version of a song from our pasts, to now help us along our own paths of self growth.

After all living is all about how we #perceive and #react to #life happening around us. To #succeed you must evolve yourself. That's the point. It's meant to #test you. To #teach you. To #mold you. If you allow it to. To push you out of your comfort zone and into the #soul you are meant to be. Life, that is. To show you happiness is a choice.

#Emerson said it best imho: "To laugh often, to win the respect of intellegent people and the affection of children, to earn the appreciation of honest critics and endure the betrayal of false friends, to appreciate beauty, to find the best in others, to leave the world a bit better, whether by a healthy child, a garden patch... To know even one life breathed easier because you have LIVED. This is to have succeeded!"

Can't you see? What you claim as misery I see as opportunity. I choose to float on the things I have successfully done in my 33 years. All because of the many unsuccessful things I had to find the lessons in along the way. I have learned. I have evolved. I have loved. Even with my past hanging on my coattails I will overcome. Because I have before. I still have many lessons ahead of me yet, and by my own standards - I have already won. That's the point. #XOXO #AC

#fir #fallinginreverse #druginmeisreimagined #growth #happiness #changeyourperception #cantyousee #checkitout #openyoureyes #thankyou #HUMANsofHUMANity #igotthis (...copied from my own instagram...)

snippet.textDisplay: Back when I was like 14 or 15 I would set a different ringtone for every contact I had in my phone, just random songs I liked. I set the original version of this song as the ringtone for my dad... The lyrics in no way describe my dad, I just liked the song so much that I had that same ringtone for like three years. I'd gotten so used to the ringtone that now everytime I hear this song it brings back memories of my dad calling. Since he passed away the day after Christmas 2018, the way this version sounds just fits now.
